snippet.textDisplay:
Khabib has NEVER beaten the same guy twice. And honestly, when you have a rivalry like Khabib/Conor, with 2 GREAT fighters, you cant really say who is the better man based on 1 fight. Things happen, fighters get lucky, fighters have bad nights, etc. This is why most rivalries have turned into a series. You gotta beat a man TWICE to truly know that you are better. Which means a second fight is basically mandatory. And sometimes a third fight, depending on the results of the second one.
Cormier vs Miocic 3 is happening because they are 1 and 1. So they need this Trilogy fight to see who is truly the better man.
But Cormier vs Jones 3 doesnt ever need to happen, because Jones beat him twice, so we know who better fighter is.
In DC's own crying words; "Well, i guess if he beat me twice, then there is no rivalry".

But we NEED another Khabib vs Conor. And if Khabib wins again, the rivalry is over. No more rematches. But if Conor wins the rematch, then we have a Trilogy to look forward to. Just like Conor wants to fight Nate again, even though Conor won their last bout.
